  "summary": "Malicious console-hijacking exfiltrator to Telegram/Firebase",
  "details": "Package `0e` replaces the global `console` with a Proxy on import that forwards logged arguments to a hardcoded Telegram Bot API endpoint (bot token 1998266306:AAFfOoMrCRQ1xE9TlaWL86PoMk3dwkLQYyY with multiple chat_ids) and PUTs serialized data to an author-controlled Firebase instance `iiilll.firebaseio.com`, confirmed by a static pattern match). It additionally ships a hardcoded imgbb API key and Telegram bot token embedded in the module. The package has no README, no documented API, no exports — its only effect is the covert side-effect hijack. This is unambiguous covert data relay to attacker-controlled infrastructure plus third-party credential redistribution.",
